This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the analysis of text complexity and the identification of adversarial text. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the limitations of current AI systems in detecting adversarial text. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it addresses the issue of attackers using adversarial text for malicious purposes. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the proposed method for identifying adversarial text involves feature extraction.
